As the epidemic continues to escalate outside China, more and more Chinese are returning home. But many face difficulties returning to their home countries because of restrictions such as the upgrading of local controls and the suspension of many international flights.

###The winding road home

At 1500 local time on March 14, Ms. Ouyang, who was scheduled to return via Moscow via Aeroflot, arrived at the Rome airport with protective gear and successfully checked in and out of the airport, but after being told before boarding that non-russians could not board the plane, "Aeroflot staff simply tore up half my boarding pass. " She was joined by about 50 Chinese. After fruitless negotiations with Aeroflot, Ms. Ouyang quickly rebooked the Ethiopian Airlines flight home via Addis Ababa. But "the airline is full at the moment, so those who don't have tickets have to go home and there are no flights left. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Rome airport, photo: Ouyang

Ouyang said she called Aeroflot's official customer service before departure to make sure her connecting flight was cleared, but was denied boarding due to a policy change at the airport. It has been verified that currently the latest policy of Aeroflot at the Rome airport is that, only citizens of the five countries of the Eurasian Economic Union (Russia, Belarus, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Armenia) are allowed to return to Moscow by Russian air.

Just a day earlier, a room lady in Italy, thanks to the introduction of Aeroflot policy before the same flight home, before the UAE, Turkish Airlines have been changed to adjust the Italian route. She wore a protective suit throughout the 22 hour flight and did not take off her mask to eat or drink to minimize the risk of infection.

In wechat groups like the European party group, people are constantly sharing their experience of returning home and updating airport restrictions. Students returning from Spain, Germany and France are keeping a close eye on flights and policy, fearing flight delays and cancellations.

The enthusiasts in the group Keep up-to-date on the points to note, "there is no connecting flight between Taipei and Singapore at the moment. From March 16, flights between Moscow and Barcelona, Burgas, Frankfurt, Heraklion, Munich, Thessaloniki and Zurich will be suspended. To get through security, you need to remove your mask and protective clothing."

In addition, there are many "return group" into the ticket sales agent group, a Dutch transfer to return to the country of business class ticket was bought nearly 50,000 yuan A.

###Flight, charter or Business?

An Air China Boeing 747-400 takes off from Beijing Capital International Airport on March 15,13:07 Beijing time, on a chartered flight from Beijing to Foshan, in Milan, Beijing. The plane's two-cabin configuration, with a maximum capacity of 524 passengers, is still a drop in the bucket compared with overseas Chinese who have a need to return home.

At present, some overseas Chinese are considering various ways to organize chartered flights to return home. A London student told interface news that the school's Federation had helped connect the CAAC A330, a direct flight from London to Tianjin, which costs # 1,400 in economy and # 3,000 in business. Parents of overseas students have also set up charter flights to count the demand for returning home, hoping to gather enough people to charter a plane to return home.

The use of European Chinese eager to return home, some criminals began to use false flight information to take advantage of fraud. The airline said in a statement on March 13 that it had not received any request for a commercial charter flight to return to Boston.

An employee of a domestic airline told the interface news that, "We do receive requests from parents of European students for charter flights, but the approval process for individual charter flights is complicated. Airlines are still focused on ensuring normal flights. "

On 4 March, the Civil Aviation Authority announced an incentive policy for non-stop and resumed international flights during the outbreak, which will be implemented from 23 January 2020 to 30 June 2020. The reward standard is divided into two categories: a total of 0.0176 yuan per flight kilometer and 0.0528 yuan per flight kilometer for Solo flights.

Thanks to CAA's incentive policies and market demand, airlines have gradually resumed some international routes. Among them, China Southern Airlines plans to gradually resume international passenger flights from Guangzhou to Australia and New Zealand, North America, Europe, Southeast Asia and other regions. Among the European routes, from March 22, China Southern Airlines plans to resume the guangzhou-london route to 4 flights per week, one, three, five, seven a week.

China Eastern has resumed several international routes since March 15. Among them, the European routes resumed the routes of Pudong -- Paris, Pudong -- Amsterdam, Pudong -- Frankfurt, Pudong -- London, etc. .

In addition to the traditional civil aviation fixed flights and charter flights, benefiting from the advantages of fast and private, business jet has become a popular option for Chinese to return home. On March 14, golden deer airlines launched the March 18 london-geneva-shanghai route 787 business trip, a total of 40 seats, a single seat starting price of 180,000 yuan, sold out quickly.

"At present, charter flights are priced at one per day, airport and immigration policies are changing at any time, passenger demand is booming, and charter flights on the platform have been scheduled for a week, " said a business jet executive

According to one quotation, the price for a single seat on a business charter flight is at least 100,000 or more. LONDON, March 19th; Shanghai, March 22nd; 13 seats, Global Express, London; Shanghai, Pudong, Shanghai, 120,000 each.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
However, with the domestic epidemic prevention policy continues to upgrade, the official plane or will face entry restrictions. At present, Beijing Capital International Airport has announced the suspension of international (including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan regions) into Hong Kong business aircraft support mission, the resumption time will be announced.

###Preventing risks of overseas import

At present, inbound international flights are still more scattered, involving the country's 24 airports, are facing greater pressure of control.

On March 14, there were 10 airports operating flights from the affected areas in China, with eight in Beijing Capital International Airport, with five in the second place, according to standard flight data. In addition, Guangzhou Baiyun, Harbin Taiping, Yanji Chaoyang Chuan to the daily average of 2 epidemic area flights ranked third.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As a key port to prevent the importation of foreign epidemic diseases, the airport has implemented very strict epidemic prevention measures. In Beijing Capital International Airport, all international and regional inbound flights stop at the Beijing Capital International Airport Disposal Zone. Passengers go through the customs for temperature measurement and other quarantine inspection, and the frontier inspection goes through the entry formalities. non-transit passengers wait in the exclusive rest area for the shuttle bus to go to the Xinguo exhibition passenger connection area. After the transit passengers go through the transit formalities, then proceed to your designated lounge area.

The Shanghai authorities have requested that, starting from zero hour on March 13, any person who enters Shanghai within 14 days prior to the date of entry, all Chinese and foreign personnel who have traveled or lived in Korea, Italy, Iran, Japan, France, Spain, Germany, the United States and other countries will be placed under home or centralized quarantine health observation.

At a press conference on March 15 on the prevention and control of the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic in Beijing, Zhang Yun, a member of the overseas epidemic prevention and control team of Air China, said the statistics were rolling from March 1 to March 15, air China flight to Beijing stopped carrying 76 passengers before boarding due to excessive body temperature, involving 23 flights. From March 1 to March 15 rolling statistics, Air China flight crew to carry out flights into Beijing, in-flight temperature detection over the ground for quarantine 67 people (involving 44 flights) .
